---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<style lang="scss">
@use '../../../assets/css/_theme.scss' as *;

.project-block {
	padding: 16px 0;
	border-bottom: 1px solid $border-subtle;

	&:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 4px;
		color: $green-dark;
	}

	.project-block__meta {
		font-family: "indivisible", sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		color: $font-light;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	p {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}
}
</style>
<Layout title="Movement Ecology" description="Erell Institute movement ecology research — how animals move, make decisions, and interact with their environment across desert ecosystems worldwide.">
	<main class="page-main">
		<div class="pure-g center">
			<div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-4-5 pure-u-lg-3-5 pure-u-xxl-1-2">
				<header class="page-header">
					<h1>Movement Ecology</h1>
					<p class="page-header__lead">
						Movement patterns characterize every animal and provide a window into that animal's
						decision-making. We study movement to examine the behavior of individuals — how they
						monitor their environment, interact socially, use habitat, forage, and avoid predators.
					</p>
				</header>

				<h2 class="section-title">Research Projects</h2>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Guadalupe Mountains National Park, Texas</div>
					<h3>Space use in blanched lesser earless lizards (<em>Holbrookia maculata</em>)</h3>
					<p>Orton et al. 2024</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Gobi Desert, Mongolia</div>
					<h3>Toad-headed agama lizards (<em>Phrynocephalus versicolor</em>) movement patterns</h3>
					<p>Utsumi et al. 2025. Collaboration with Bazartseren Boldgiv, National University of Mongolia.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Sahara Desert, Tunisia</div>
					<h3>Niche partitioning among three racerunner species (<em>Acanthodactylus</em>)</h3>
					<p>Eifler et al. 2023</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Great Basin Desert, Oregon</div>
					<h3>Cooccurring lizard species habitat use</h3>
					<p>McAlpine-Bellis et al. 2023</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Great Basin Desert, Oregon</div>
					<h3>Long-nosed leopard lizards (<em>Gambelia wislizenii</em>) movement</h3>
					<p>Garrison et al. 2017</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Chihuahuan Desert, Colorado</div>
					<h3>Checkered whiptails (<em>Aspidoscelis neotellatus</em>) movement and foraging</h3>
					<p>Kusaka et al. 2021; Utsumi et al. 2020</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Namib Desert</div>
					<h3>Dune lizards (<em>Meroles anchietae</em>) space use</h3>
					<p>Eifler et al. 2020</p>
				</div>

				<div class="project-block">
					<div class="project-block__meta">Atacama Desert, Chile</div>
					<h3>Escape behavior and habitat use — blanched lesser earless lizards</h3>
					<p>How do lizards escape when they live between the Atacama Desert and the Pacific Ocean?</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
